        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 24 at 5:57PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 557 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Ramah, or 27 miles southwest of Limon, moving south at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Heavy rain, wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Ramah.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
